@Simon Brandhof, I&#39;m confused on why a carriage return would be counted as another line?  A &quot;
&quot; is a Carriage return line feed, so whoever writes &quot;
&quot; is not understanding something... Plus he is searching char by char, so I&#39;m pretty sure if someone were to use &quot;
&quot; it would still catch the &quot;
&quot; and count the line. Either way  I think he made the point just fine. However, their are many scenarios where this is not a sufficient way to get a line count.
